        public GeosearchLocations search(java.lang.String searchText,
                                 java.lang.String latitude,
                                 java.lang.String longitude,
                                 java.lang.String searchRadius,
                                 java.lang.String searchRadiusUnit,
                                 java.lang.String maxCandidates,
                                 java.lang.String country,
                                 java.lang.String matchOnAddressNumber,
                                 java.lang.String autoDetectLocation,
                                 java.lang.String ipAddress,
                                 java.lang.String areaName1,
                                 java.lang.String areaName3,
                                 java.lang.String postCode,
                                 java.lang.String returnAdminAreasOnly,
                                 java.lang.String includeRangesDetails,
                                 java.lang.String searchType,
                                 java.lang.String searchOnAddressNumber)
                          throws ApiException
        Typeahead Search Performs search to retrieve list of places by input text and location vicinity.
        Parameters:
        searchText - The input to be searched. (required)
        latitude - Latitude of the location. Either the latitude or the longitude must be provided. (optional)
        longitude - Longitude of the location. Either the latitude or the longitude must be provided. (optional)
        searchRadius - Radius range within which search is performed. (optional)
        searchRadiusUnit - Radius unit such as Feet, Kilometers, Miles or Meters. (optional)
        maxCandidates - Maximum number of addresses that can be retrieved. (optional)
        country - Country ISO code. We need to make sure that either Lat/Lng or Country is provided to API (optional)
        matchOnAddressNumber - Option so that we force api to match on address number (optional)
        autoDetectLocation - Option to allow API to detect origin of API request automatically (optional, default to true)
        ipAddress - (optional)
        areaName1 - State province of the input to be searched (optional)
        areaName3 - City of the input to be searched (optional)
        postCode - Postal Code of the input to be searched (optional)
        returnAdminAreasOnly - if value set 'Y' then it will only do a matching on postcode or areaName1, areaName2, areaName3 and areaName4 fields in the data (optional, default to N)
        includeRangesDetails - if value set 'Y' then display all unit info of ranges, if value set 'N' then don't show ranges (optional, default to Y)
        searchType - Preference to control search type of interactive requests. (optional, default to ADDRESS)
        searchOnAddressNumber - if value set 'Y' then display searchOnAddressNumber (optional, default to N)
        Returns:
        GeosearchLocations
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body
